    "## 1.4 Scope and Domain of Validity\n",
    "\n",
    "The engine operates within a defined envelope of physical conditions and system types.\n",
    "\n",
    "**In scope:**\n",
    "- Molecular formation at thermodynamic equilibrium (NVE, NVT ensembles)\n",
    "- Cluster formation: $N = 2$ to $N \\approx 10{,}000$ particles\n",
    "- Temperature range: 50 K to 1000 K (condensed-phase and gas-phase)\n",
    "- Bond inference from interatomic distance and covalent radii\n",
    "- VSEPR-based geometry prediction as initialization heuristic\n",
    "- Formation scoring, classification, and cataloging\n",
    "- Deterministic reproducibility from seed-controlled runs\n",
    "- Self-audit: failure classification, coverage targeting, regression detection\n",
    "\n",
    "**Out of scope (by design, not by accident):**\n",
    "- Quantum tunneling, zero-point energy, exchange-correlation\n",
    "- Reactive bond dynamics (bond breaking/formation during MD) — the bond graph is currently static during a simulation run, though the reaction engine (§8) proposes reactions between runs\n",
    "- Grand canonical ensemble ($\\mu VT$), pressure-controlled ensemble (NPT)\n",
    "- Electronic excited states, photochemistry\n",
    "- Relativistic effects (relevant for $Z > 80$)\n",
    "- Systems requiring explicit solvent with polarizable models\n",
    "\n",
    "These boundaries are not apologies. They define the regime where the methodology produces reliable results and distinguish it from the regime where it does not."
