    "## 4.1 Unit System and Physical Constants\n",
    "\n",
    "The internal unit system must be stated once and never varied, because unit inconsistency is the single most common source of catastrophic failure in molecular simulation. The framework uses the \"real\" unit system, standard in AMBER and LAMMPS:\n",
