    "## 5.3 FIRE Minimization\n",
    "\n",
    "The formation pipeline requires finding local minima of the potential energy surface. The engine uses the Fast Inertial Relaxation Engine (FIRE) of Bitzek et al. (2006), a damped molecular dynamics scheme that is robust, parameter-insensitive, and does not require Hessian computation.\n",
    "\n",
    "FIRE treats the minimization as a dynamics problem: particles are given velocities, and those velocities are continuously steered toward the downhill direction on the energy surface.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Velocity mixing** — after every step, the velocity is blended with the force direction:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\mathbf{v}_i \\leftarrow (1-\\alpha)\\,\\mathbf{v}_i + \\alpha\\,|\\mathbf{v}|\\,\\hat{\\mathbf{F}}_i\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where $\\hat{\\mathbf{F}}_i = \\mathbf{F}_i / |\\mathbf{F}|_{\\text{global}}$ is the normalized force and $|\\mathbf{v}| = \\sqrt{\\sum_i |\\mathbf{v}_i|^2}$ is the global speed. The parameter $\\alpha$ controls how aggressively velocities are aligned with forces.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Power monitoring** — the dot product $P = \\sum_i \\mathbf{v}_i \\cdot \\mathbf{F}_i$ measures whether the system is going downhill ($P > 0$) or uphill ($P \\leq 0$):\n",
    "\n",
    "- $P > 0$: keep going. After $n_\\text{min}$ consecutive positive steps, increase $\\Delta t$ (accelerate) and decrease $\\alpha$ (trust the trajectory more).\n",
    "- $P \\leq 0$: overshoot detected. Freeze (set $\\mathbf{v} = 0$), decrease $\\Delta t$ (slow down), reset $\\alpha$ to initial value.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Position update** — simple explicit Euler: $\\mathbf{x}_i \\leftarrow \\mathbf{x}_i + \\Delta t \\cdot \\mathbf{v}_i$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Convergence** — the minimization terminates when either:\n",
    "- RMS force falls below threshold: $F_\\text{rms} = \\sqrt{\\frac{1}{N}\\sum_i |\\mathbf{F}_i|^2} < \\epsilon_F$\n",
    "- Energy change per atom falls below threshold: $|\\Delta U|/N < \\epsilon_U$\n",
    "- Maximum iterations reached\n",
    "\n",
    "| Parameter | Default | Role |\n",
    "|-----------|---------|------|\n",
    "| $\\Delta t_0$ | $10^{-3}$ | Initial step size |\n",
    "| $\\alpha_0$ | 0.1 | Initial velocity-force mixing |\n",
    "| $f_\\text{inc}$ | 1.1 | Timestep growth factor |\n",
    "| $f_\\text{dec}$ | 0.5 | Timestep shrink factor |\n",
    "| $f_\\alpha$ | 0.99 | Alpha decay rate |\n",
    "| $n_\\text{min}$ | 5 | Steps before adaptation |\n",
    "| $\\Delta t_\\text{max}$ | $10^{-1}$ | Timestep ceiling |\n",
    "| $\\epsilon_F$ | $10^{-6}$ | Force convergence |\n",
    "| $\\epsilon_U$ | $10^{-10}$ | Energy convergence (per atom) |\n",
    "\n",
    "FIRE's role in the formation pipeline is critical. It is the operation that converts a dynamical trajectory into a structural result. MD explores; FIRE finalizes."
