    "---\n",
    "# §10 — Multiscale Projection and Constructed States\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 10.1 Scale Transitions\n",
    "\n",
    "The formation engine operates at the atomistic scale by default ($N = 2$–$10{,}000$). Larger systems require either explicit supercell construction or coarse-grained representations.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Supercell Construction\n",
    "\n",
    "Given a unit cell with $N$ atoms and lattice vectors $(\\mathbf{a}, \\mathbf{b}, \\mathbf{c})$, the supercell with replication $(n_a, n_b, n_c)$ contains $N \\times n_a \\times n_b \\times n_c$ atoms:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\mathbf{r}_{i,pqr} = \\mathbf{r}_i + p\\,\\mathbf{a} + q\\,\\mathbf{b} + r\\,\\mathbf{c}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "for $p \\in [0, n_a)$, $q \\in [0, n_b)$, $r \\in [0, n_c)$.\n",
    "\n",
    "All atomic properties (mass, charge, type) are replicated identically. The supercell lattice vectors become $n_a\\mathbf{a}, n_b\\mathbf{b}, n_c\\mathbf{c}$.\n",
    "\n",
    "After construction, the supercell is typically relaxed via FIRE minimization to remove artificial strain from the periodic replication. The complete construction history (supercell + relax) is recorded in the xyzC recipe.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Coarse-Graining and Bulk Properties\n",
    "\n",
    "The xyzC format reserves slots for coarse-grained representations (bead count, bead types, PMF reference) and bulk properties (density, elastic modulus, RDF reference). These are placeholders: the mapping from atomistic to coarse-grained is defined in the file format but not yet implemented in the simulation engine.\n",
    "\n",
    "All reserved slots are initialized to null. They must never contain default or placeholder values that could be mistaken for computed data."
   ]
  },
