    "---\n",
    "# §11 — Deterministic Pipeline and Self-Audit\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 11.1 Reproducibility as Non-Negotiable Property\n",
    "\n",
    "Every formation produced by this engine must be reproducible from its inputs alone. Given:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "(\\text{formula}, \\; \\text{seed}, \\; \\text{parameters})\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "the engine must produce bit-identical output. This requires:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Seed-controlled RNG (`std::mt19937`) for all stochastic elements\n",
    "2. Index-ordered force evaluation (no thread-dependent accumulation)\n",
    "3. Deterministic floating-point semantics (IEEE 754 compliance, no fast-math flags that reorder operations)\n",
    "4. Fixed library versions (no behavioral changes between runs)\n",
    "\n",
    "If two runs of the same input produce different output, the engine has a defect. There is no \"acceptable non-determinism.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "## 11.2 Failure Classification\n",
    "\n",
    "The self-audit system categorizes every failed simulation run into one of six buckets by pattern-matching on the output:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Category | Signature | Root Cause |\n",
    "|----------|-----------|------------|\n",
    "| NUMERICAL | NaN, inf, overflow | Timestep too large, singularity |\n",
    "| PHYSICS | Clash explosion, unphysical bonds | Atoms initialized too close |\n",
    "| OOD | Undefined parameters, unsupported composition | Element outside UFF coverage |\n",
    "| CONVERGENCE | FIRE stalled, energy plateau | Flat landscape, inadequate parameters |\n",
    "| TIMEOUT | Wall-clock exceeded | System too large for allocated time |\n",
    "| UNKNOWN | None of the above | New failure mode — triggers investigation |\n",
    "\n",
    "Each failure stores a minimal reproduction command: the exact CLI invocation that triggers the failure, with seed and parameters. The UNKNOWN category must remain below 5% of total failures; if it exceeds this threshold, the classification patterns need updating.\n",
    "\n",
    "## 11.3 Coverage-Driven Exploration\n",
    "\n",
    "The gap targeter partitions the parameter space into a 3D grid:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Scale: $[2, 5, 10, 20, 50, 100]$ atoms (6 bins)\n",
    "- Temperature: $[50, 100, \\ldots, 500]$ K (10 bins)\n",
    "- Density: $[0.001, 0.012, \\ldots, 0.1]$ g/cm³ (10 bins)\n",
    "\n",
    "Total: 600 cells. A cell is **sparse** if it has fewer than 10 runs. A cell has **high mismatch** if its mean energy differs from its neighbor's by more than $0.5\\sigma$.\n",
    "\n",
    "The gap targeter schedules new runs in sparse and mismatched cells, progressively filling the parameter space until coverage exceeds 95%.\n",
    "\n",
    "## 11.4 Regression Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "When parameters change, the regression detector reruns a benchmark suite and compares results:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Reclassifications**: molecules that changed stability class (stable → unstable)\n",
    "- **Score deltas**: $|\\Delta S| > 0.01$\n",
    "- **Invariant violations**: energy non-monotonic during relaxation, bond count oscillation, score out of bounds, classification inconsistency\n",
    "\n",
    "The regression detector produces a binary verdict: ✅ NO REGRESSIONS or ⚠️ REVIEW REQUIRED. Parameter changes that cause regressions are not accepted until the regressions are understood and either fixed or documented as acceptable."
