    "## 12.1 Thermodynamic Sanity\n",
    "\n",
    "Before any formation result is trusted, the integration machinery must pass fundamental physical tests:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Test | Criterion | Physics |\n",
    "|------|-----------|--------|\n",
    "| NVE energy conservation | $|\\Delta E|/N < 10^{-3}$ kcal/mol over $10^4$ steps | Symplecticity of velocity Verlet |\n",
    "| NVT temperature | $|\\langle T\\rangle - T_\\text{target}|/T_\\text{target} < 0.05$ | Fluctuation-dissipation balance |\n",
    "| Equipartition | $\\langle K\\rangle \\approx \\frac{3}{2}Nk_BT$ | Correct temperature definition |\n",
    "| Momentum conservation | $|\\mathbf{P}(t) - \\mathbf{P}(0)| < 10^{-10}$ (NVE) | Newton's third law |\n",
    "| Ideal gas limit | $P \\approx Nk_BT/V$ for dilute noble gas | Virial equation |\n",
    "\n",
    "If any of these fail, the engine has a defect in its force evaluation, integration, or thermodynamic computation. Formation results produced by defective machinery are invalid.\n",
    "\n",
    "## 12.2 Formation Reproducibility\n",
    "\n",
    "| Test | Method | Criterion |\n",
    "|------|--------|----------|\n",
    "| Seed determinism | Same inputs × 10 runs | Bit-identical output |\n",
    "| Minimum stability | Perturb minimum + re-minimize | Returns to same minimum (RMSD < 0.01 Å) |\n",
    "| Basin consistency | 100 random starts → FIRE | Energy distribution converges |\n",
    "\n",
    "## 12.3 Known Failure Modes\n",
    "\n",
    "| Failure | Root Cause | Mitigation |\n",
    "|---------|-----------|------------|\n",
    "| NaN in forces | Atom overlap $r < 0.1$ Å | Skip pair at minimum distance |\n",
    "| Temperature explosion (ionic MD) | Coulomb-integrator coupling | Coulomb forces disabled in MD loop |\n",
    "| FIRE non-convergence | Flat energy landscape | Report max-steps, score with $w_S = 0.3$ |\n",
    "| Bond count oscillation | Distance threshold sensitivity | Fixed tolerance $f = 1.2$ |\n",
    "\n",
    "Every known failure mode has a documented mitigation. Undocumented failures trigger investigation and are not silently tolerated."
